Normal behavior is typical behavior.  One cannot change the definition
of normal by making by enacting law that makes typical behavior illegal.

Let's say that the normal walking pace of an adult was 3.5 mph.  If a
law is enacted that specifies an absolute speed limit of 2 mph on
sidewalks, then a 3.5 mph walking pace does not automatically become
abnormal behavior.

Similarly, if posted limits were 70 mph on Virginia interstates (as they
were in 1972), and most traffic drove at 70 mph at that time, then
that's what normal speed was.  Driving at 70 mph did not suddenly become
abnormal behavior at the beginning of 1974 when the speed limit changed
to 55 mph.
