Guardenman wrote:
&gt; Sorry my bad I should have said 46.2-823 (not 824).
">

The 46.2 part refers to *title* 46.2.
The 8xx part refers to *chapter* 8.

The last 2 numbers refer to articles.  The ten's digit, in some cases,
refer to a series of articles.

46.2-82x series deals with right of way at intersections, roundabouts,
and merge points.

46.2-83x deals with heeding signage and traffic control devices (at
least through 835.

46.4-84x deals with overtaking (at least the first 4 parts)

46.4-85x deals with forms of reckless driving.

Since 46.2-823 falls under the section dealing with intersection right
of way, that's what it applies to (since the text of the law itself
states "...he might otherwise have under this *article*."

Had that particular (sub)article stated "...under this *chapter*," then
your interpretation would be correct.  IOW, the law you cited has
nothing to do with yielding the passing lane (IOW, any other lane
besides the right most lane on a multilane highway), when the vehicle
behind signals as much.
