Not in this case.  The code of Virginia is divided into title,
*chapter*, article, statute.  There are several statutes that make
reference to a numbered article and then point to a particular statute
and note that it starts a sequence ("et seq.") of statutes.

The phrase "this article" will refer to the article that the statute is
located within.  The phrase "this chapter" will refer to the chapter
that the statute is located within.  The phrase "this title" will refer
to the title that the statute is located within.
