In order to impede traffic, one must drive in such a way that traffic
behind them has no choice but to slow down.  A truck going 45 mph in the
right lane of an interstate while ascending a grade will not impede
traffic since traffic can easily maintain speed and pass him in the left
lane.  If there are two trucks both going 45 mph up the same grade, and
one of them is in the left lane besides the other, then the one in the
left lane is impeding traffic.  It's also unlawful for that truck to
remain in the left lane after one of the vehicles behind him uses some
form of visible or audible signal (after he's able to move to the right
