tailgating each other, and me, and that makes me very very nervous, so
I avoid cruising in the lefthand lane when speeds start getting into
the highly illegal lunatic range...

But, during rush hours, when traffic across the San Gabriel and San
Fernando valleys is at its peak, the left lane is regulated down to the
speed limit or less by the sheer VOLUME of traffic. Every lane is
needed to move the massive volume of rush hour traffic. California
CANNOT afford the luxury of reserving the left lane for speeders
only...

At that point, most of the left lane speed demons are resigned to the
fact that they just are NOT going to get around a lane of
bumper-to-bumper cars stretching from horizon to horizon. And the
majority of the morons are smart enough to quit changing lanes and
jockeying for position...

