lengths is an invitation to move into it and tailgate the car ahead of
them. The 8 car length space you hypothesized would not exist for very
long on the Ventura freeway or the San Bernardino freeway from 7AM to
9AM or 3PM to 6PM...

But you wanted to talked about who is WRONG in the hypothetical case
you proposed. The cars passing on the right of the driver cruising at
the posted speed limit are in the WRONG, if they are exceeding the
maximum speed limit. They are not wrong for passing on the right, since
passing on the right is not illegal on California freeways...

Now, I'll address how the bunch of right hand passers got into the #2
lane in the first place to try to pass the law-abiding driver
proceeding at the speed limit. The #2 lane is an endless stream of
other law-abiding drivers who are doing what the #1 lane driver is
accused of. They are driving at the speed limit and they won't go any
faster. The law-abiders in the #2 lane are a wall of moving metal
restricting the scofflaws from easily moving around the law-abiding
driver to grab that precious few hundred feet of "fast lane" for
themselves...

