&gt; Good show and nice research Arif!  Any clue what Atwell v. Watson was
&gt; all about?  (just curious)
">

Basically, Atwell was a passenger who was injured in a vehicle collision
resulting from Watson pulling out in front of the vehicle Atwell was
riding in (Watson was taking a left turn from a side street).

Several witnesses stated that Goodwin (the driver of the car Atwell was
riding in) was travelling at an "excessive" speed though both Atwell and
Goodwin stated that they were proceeding at a "normal" speed.  The lower
court ruling was in favor of Watson.  The Virginia Supreme Court
overturned the ruling because the section of code that applied to the
right-of-way situation in this case did not have the "speeder loses the
right of way" clause.
