I'd like to see _why_ they use public transport before saying that its all that
great an idea.  If its all they can afford, then it not something that would
work all that well here.  Here, the system has to be _better_, in terms of its
speed, to win the transport battle.  People won't fall all over themselves to
ride it _just_ to save $2 - $5 a day and spend an extra 30 minutes waiting on
